Matplotlib - Theory in Hinglish:
ğŸ”¹ Matplotlib ek Python library hai jo data ko visually represent karne ke liye use hoti hai, especially graphs aur charts banane ke liye.

ğŸ”¹ Ye mainly 2D plotting ke liye famous hai, aur scientific graphs banane ke liye widely use hoti hai.

ğŸ”¹ Iska main module pyplot hai, jisko generally import matplotlib.pyplot as plt ke naam se import karte hain.

ğŸ“Š Commonly Used Plot Types:
Line Plot â€“ data points ko line se jodta hai.
plt.plot(x, y)

Bar Chart â€“ categorical data ke liye.
plt.bar(x, height)

Histogram â€“ data ke distribution ko dikhata hai.
plt.hist(data)

Scatter Plot â€“ 2 variables ke relation ko show karta hai.
plt.scatter(x, y)

Pie Chart â€“ percentage ya proportion dikhata hai.
plt.pie(data)

ğŸ› ï¸ Important Functions:
plt.title() â†’ Graph ka title set karta hai.

plt.xlabel() / plt.ylabel() â†’ X aur Y axis ka label set karta hai.

plt.legend() â†’ Graph ke elements ka label show karta hai.

plt.grid() â†’ Graph mein grid lines add karta hai.

plt.show() â†’ Graph ko screen pe show karta hai.
